Blocks.childText: HYMNS FROM "WINDOWS OF HEAVEN" SONG BOOK. THE PRIZE IS SET BEFORE US. Let those refuse to sing Who never knew our God; The prize is set before us- But children of the heav'nly King, To win, our Lord implores us! But children of the heav'nly King, The eye of God is o'er us, May speak their joys abroad, From on high, from on high! May speak their joys abroad. His loving tones are falling, While sin is dark, appaling; The hill of Zion yields 'Tis Jesus gently calling- A thousand sacred sweets, He is nigh, He is nigh. Before we reach the heaven'ly fields, CH0.-By and by we shall meet Him, Before we reach the heaven'ly fields, By and by we shall greet Him, Or walk the golden streets, And with Jesus reign in glory, Or walk the golden streets. By and by, by and by; By and by we shall meet Him, Then let our song abound, By and by we shall greet Him, And every tear be dry; And with Jesus reign in glory, We're marching through Immanuel's ground, By and by. We're marching through Immanuel's ground, To fairer worlds on high. We follow where He leadeth- To fairer worlds on high. We pasture where He feedeth- We yield to Him who pleadeth From on high, from on high! For naught from Him can sever; LET THE SAVIOUR IN. Our hope shall brighten ever; And faith shall fail us never- There's a Stranger at the door; He is nigh, He is nigh. Let Him in! Our home is bright above us; He has been there oft before; No trials there to move us, Let Him in! But Christ our Lord to love us, Let Him in ere He is gone; Dwells on high: dwells on high! Let Him in, The Holy One, We give our best endeavor; Jesus Christ, the Father's Son; We praise His name forever; Let Him in! His precious words can never- Never die, never die. Open now to Him your heart; Let Him in! If you wait He will depart; BETHANY. Let Him in! Let Him in; He is your Friend; Nearer, my God, to Thee, And your soul He will defend, Nearer to Thee! He will keep you to the end; E'en though it be a cross Let Him in! That raiseth me, Still all my song shall be, Hear you now His loving voice; Let Him in! Nearer, my God, to Thee, Nearer to Thee! Now, oh now, make Him your choice; Let Him in! Though like a wanderer, He is standing at the door, The sun gone down, Joy to you He will restore, Darkness comes over me, And His name you will adore; My rest a stone; Let Him in! Yet in my dreams I'd be Now admit the heav'nly Guest; Nearer, my God, to Thee, Let Him in! Nearer to Thee. He will make for you a feast; There let my way appear Let Him in! Steps unto heaven; He will speak your sins forgin'n, All that Thou sendest me And when earth-ties all are riv'n, In mercy given; He will take you home to heav'n. Let Him in! Angels to beckon me Nearer. my God, to Thee, Nearer to Thee! Or, if on joyful wing, CORONATION. Cleaving the sky, Sun, moon, and stars forgot, All hail the power of Jesus' name! Upward I fly, Let angels prostrate fall; Still all my song shall be, Bring forth the royal diadem, Nearer, my God, to Thee, And crown Him Lord of all. Nearer to Thee. Ye chosen seed of Israel's race, WE'RE MARCHING TO ZION. Ye ransomed from the fall, Hail Him who saves you by His grace, Come we that love the Lord, And crown Him Lord of all. And let our joys be known, Join in a song with sweet accord, Sinners, whose love can ne'er forget Join in a song with sweet accord, The wormwood and the gall, And thus surround the throne. Go, spread your trophies at His feet, And thus surround the throne. And crown Him Lord of all. CHO.-We're marching to Zion, Let every kindred, every tribe, Beautiful, beautiful, Zion; On this terrestrial ball, We're marching upward to Zion, To Him all majesty ascribe, The beautiful city of God. And crown Him Lord of all. MEETINGS EVERY NIGHT NEXT WEEK AT BRANTLY CHURCH, Corner Schroeder Street and Edmondson Ave. NOONDAY MEETINGS AT 12 CLOCK EVERY DAY AT St. John's Independent Methodist Church, Liberty Street near Lexington. COME COME I
